      <hedline>
        <hl1>SAFE-SEX LIES</hl1>
      </hedline>
    </body.head>
    <body.content>
      <block class="lead_paragraph">
        <p>I appreciate Meghan Daum's honesty about her difficulty in practicing safer sex consistently ("Safe-Sex Lies," Jan. 21). I am glad her difficulties don't include a desperate search for medication to control intractable diarrhea, fears that her insurance company will not pay for treatments that keep her from going  blind and panic over telling her children that she cannot care for them much longer. Many of the H.I.V.-infected people I work with used to have the same issues as Daum does. Now they have others.</p>
        <p>LAURA C. DAMSON, C.S.W. New York</p>
      </block>
